						               													<description>Wolsung: The Boardgame is a large family game for 2 to 4 players. They act as inventors and industrialists living in a fictional steampunk world, largely similar to the Victorian times. The inventors develop extraordinary constructions &amp;ndash; steam cars, golems and zeppelins &amp;ndash; in the race for the title of the best designer at the World&amp;rsquo;s Fair.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The objective of the game is to build the best and the most unique machines &amp;ndash; players compete against each other for plans of the devices as well as for the resources necessary to build them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game contains multiple elements: the board, auxiliary boards (players&amp;rsquo; workshops), a 55-card deck, numerous tokens and wooden markers and a surprise gadget being the key element of the game mechanics.&amp;#10;The board game constitutes the first product of the Wolsung Project, which includes publishing a modern role-playing game &amp;quot;Wolsung: Magic of the Steampunk Age&amp;quot; (in Polish) as well as other games and expansion packs to them and gadgets such as playing card decks and special dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game contains the following components:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- the board&amp;#10;- 3 combines&amp;#10;- the deck of 55 cards&amp;#10;- 4 workshops&amp;#10;- 84 wooden worker tokens&amp;#10;- 76 wooden resource tokens&amp;#10;- 12 wooden upgrade tokens&amp;#10;- 1 round marker&amp;#10;- 1 first engineer marker&amp;#10;- the rulebook&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
